arcane - qmk keyboard configuration
===================================
arcane is a flashy mechanical keyboard configuration make with qmk.  arcane
features split reactive backlighting with a base qwerty layout and macros and
special keys located for vim programming.

Installation
------------
arcane can be built and flashed with the following commands:

    $ # download qmk firmware from zsa, compiler, teensy loader for flashing
    $ [ ! -d 'qmk_firmware' ] && \ 
        git clone --recurse-submodules https://github.com/zsa/qmk_firmware/
    # pacman -Qq avr-gcc           >/dev/null || pacman -S avr-gcc
    # pacman -Qq teensy_loader_cli >/dev/null || pacman -S teensy_loader_cli
    $
    $ # downgrade compiler if ahead of version 8
    # [ "$(pacman -Q avr-gcc | cut -d. -f1)" != "avr-gcc 8" ] && \
        pacman -U https://archive.archlinux.org/packages/ \
	a/avr-gcc/avr-gcc-8.3.0-1-x86_64.pkg.tar.xz
    $
    $ # install flashing rules, download, build, flash arcane
    $ cd qmk_firmware; rm -rf arcane
    # [ ! -f /etc/udev/rules.d/50-qmk.rules ] && \
        cp util/udev/50-qmk.rules /etc/udev/rules.d/
    $ git clone https://github.com/arcnyxx/arcane/
    $ mv arcane keyboards/ergodox_ez/shine/keymaps/
    $ make -j 1 ergodox_ez/shine:arcane:flash


Usage
-----
arcane causes flashing lights upon keypress.  To temporarily disable this
functionality, press the key in the middle of the bottom layer on the left side
of the keyboard.

Configuration
-------------
arcane can be configured by editing the keymap.c file and (re)compiling the
source code.  This keeps it fast, simple, and secure.
